The paper deals with security and privacy issues in a virtual reality learning environment, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of design principles to enhance the resilience of the system, which could fall under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of stochastic timed automata for statistical model checking could also fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
